    - text: "The Scope-boundedness rating cites verifiable greps as evidence boundaries are testable. The grep 'docs/pipeline.md|docs/sdk.md|docs/mcp-contract.md' --include='*.py' --include='*.sh' is claimed to catch both cli.py:268 and bin/cortex-check-parity:59. It does not — bin/cortex-check-parity has no extension, so the include filter excludes it."
      origin: primary
    - text: "The body claims the pipeline-not-a-skill callout at docs/agentic-layer.md:64 reads 'internal reference, not a user-facing skill' — but the actual line reads 'pipeline is not a user-facing skill and has no entry in skills/. It is an internal Python orchestration module...'. The quoted text and the file disagree."
      origin: primary
    - text: "The Scope-boundedness rating relies on an out-of-scope enumeration that cites requirements/project.md:7 as 'F-12 dropped post-critical-review (line already balanced)', but the body and the parent epic both quote different phrasings for that line that disagree with each other and with current file content."
      origin: primary
    - text: "The Requirements-alignment 'No conflicts detected' rating overlooks a cross-child coupling: requirements/pipeline.md:130's stale claude/reference/output-floors.md reference (in #166's stale-path scope) sits adjacent to requirements/project.md:36's output-filters.conf reference (retired in parallel by #168). The deprecated-pattern-files cluster spans two siblings; the assessment treated them as cleanly partitioned."
      origin: primary
